accessibility.text: A system of linear equations is when we have two or more linear equations working together
For the equations to \"work together\" they share one or more variables
It’s a race between you and a horse. You can run 0.2 km every minute. The horse can run 0.5 km every minute. But it takes 6 minutes to saddle the horse. Let ￼ denote distance and ￼ denote time.
We have a system of equations (that are linear):
